message: I like 90s electronica: Chicane, Live at the Palladium & Euphoria: 1. It's expansive and the beat keeps me going from 2 am 'til sun up.
what do the coders listen to while they're working? I've been enjoying deadmau5 - 4x4=12, shiny toy guns, skrillex and zola jesus.
yesterday i listened to def leppard - pyromania, pig destroyer - terrorizer and Hank Williams III :)
today is dylan's "bringing it all back home", iggy pop's "lust for life", and a lot of colin stetson's new lp
I'm actually jealous.  It'd be awesome to be able to listen to music when I do homework etc.

Stereolab!!  dots and loops, cobra and phases, others... great upbeat polyrhythms keep my mind moving.  Also, sometimes when I want minimal distractions, ~15th century vocal polyphony (Josquin Desprez, etc)
I'm listening to Muse right now, yesterday lots of Radiohead and NIN
I can't get any work done when music is playing, much less music as attention grabbing as dylan and iggy pop
@kevinflo do you prefer to work in silence?
@mwhooker Well I don't really prefer it, I just have to.  If there is any music on I can't concentrate.
@mwhooker I'm sitting in the library right now actually haha.  I practically live here when the semester gets intense (like it is right now)
@kevinflo that's rough. silence is very hard to come by in my experience

I find that nice repetitive music without lyrics actually helps me concentrate, particularly in a sometimes noisy office.  I actually like the seamlessness of a mixed DJ set, and one of my favorites is the Trance Lab podcast (http://trancelab.com).  It's not really trance, but all generally enjoyable.
usually some ~140 bpm techno mixtape, it's inspiring but doesn't distract you from the code
I go through phases, but find that Trent Reznor's instrumental albums (Ghosts and the Social Network soundtrack) are in heavy rotation.
@kevinflo i'm the same way.  have you tried simplynoise.com?
Back in my coding days I liked listening to live Grateful Dead, especially long trippy jams--hours would go by like minutes
@mtoymil No, but that's quite awesome.  I'll have to try it out

I tend to stick to primarily instrumental albums, Deadmau5,  Trent Reznor/NIN(Ghosts and The Social Network soundtrack), Cloudkicker (http://cloudkicker.bandcamp.com), or some of my friend's stuff from http://mouseplanet.co.uk (Every Minute of Every Day is a favorite)
Daft Punk is usually my first go-to. I try to avoid anything with too many vocals to prevent it from distracting me.
I like Tiesto's Club Life podcast -- http://538.tiestoworld.nl/, also Daft Punk, deadmau5, & the new Glitch Mob album which is amazing
Oh and also some chiptune. Random is my favorite -- http://randomizer.se/

good topic! lately i've been gravitating towards demoscene tunes and videogame music, mars volta, mogwai, 65dos, nin, dan deacon, best fwends, death set... i sometimes throw on a recording of rain if music is too distracting.
@mickm Good call on video game music. I'll admit I sometimes really enjoy the techno remixes people do of old-school Mega Man music.
